Bristol-Myers Squibb sued generic
drugmaker Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. in federal court
in Delaware alleging infringement of a U.S. patent for
Baraclude, used to treat hepatitis B viral infections.  To contact the reporter on this story:
